SIMPLE: overthrow
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overthrow
<hw>O`ver*throw"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Overthrew</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Overthrown</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overthrowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
throw over; to overturn; to upset; to turn upside down.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His wife <qex>overthrew</qex> the table.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cause to fall or to fail; to subvert; to defeat;
to make a ruin of; to destroy; <as>as, to <ex>overthrow</ex> a
government</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the walls of Thebes he <qex>overthrew</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Gloucester] that seeks to <qex>overthrow</qex> religion.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>To throw (a baseball) beyond;
to throw too high and too far; to overshoot{1}; <as>as, the shortstop
<ex>overthrew</ex> the first baseman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To demolish; overturn; prostrate; destroy; ruin;
subvert; overcome; conquer; defeat; discomfit; vanquish; beat;
rout.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overthrow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overthrow
<hw>O"ver*throw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of overthrowing; the state of being overthrown; ruin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your sudden <qex>overthrow</qex> much rueth me.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1025 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>The act of
throwing a ball too high, as over a player's head.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Cricket)</fld> <def>A faulty return of the ball by a fielder, so
that the striker makes an additional run.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overthwart</ent>⟦br⟧
